 and theoretically engaged analysis will interest not only students and scholars of Japan but also readers of gay studies, literary studies, gender studies, and cultural studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHomosexuality and literaturezJapan. 0aHomosexuality in literature. 0aHomosexualityzJapanxHistory. 0aLegal literaturezJapanxHistory. 0aLove in literature. 0aMedical literaturezJapanxHistory and criticism. 4aGender Studies. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aPflugfelder, Gregory M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025165640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094087140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940871423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940871/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles